lead_paragraph: No wonder Lucas Pouille looked dumbfounded at his 6-4 4-6 3-6 6-4 10-8 win on Monday over fellow young gun Bernard Tomic. He had never before won a five-set match at tour level and had never beaten a seeded player at a grand slam.

headline.print_headline: Over-Achiever Pouille Setting His Sights Higher
